  "body": "<p>One of my favorite products that Amy has released has got to be the <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00I99RKI4/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;creativeASIN=B00I99RKI4&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=wwwamytangeri-20&amp;linkId=K5FGNEFSWAZ7ASGF\">stitching templates</a>! I love making fun, simple, one of a kind cards using nothing more than the template, some thread and white card stock. Sometimes I will also add a small sentiment as well, but seriously folks it doesn't get easier! </p><p>I start with my card base and decide which template to use. For this baby shower card  (baby boy!) I decided to use blues and greens so I picked out some of my favorites from my thread stash (this is actually the kids friendship bracelet kit, don't tell anyone!).</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257199574-0OMN9XW0QRZF54HUD6J9/5a-Baby%2BShower%2Bcard%2Bby%2BShanna.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Once I have pierced the holes using the Amy Tangerine template I just started with one balloon and worked my way around. I love that the balloons have the stripes, it just adds a special little touch! I am a fan of using washi on the back side to secure everything, easy and FUN!</p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n\n\n<img alt=\"5b-B2.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257232356-VRKK4F9ZIVW3AZAOI0IK/5b-B2.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"5c-B3.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257232290-E9NSXZUPBWY0PZ5K3K0F/5c-B3.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<img alt=\"5d-B4.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257233798-QSDHILFGPJEILR0QS48C/5d-B4.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<img alt=\"5e-b5.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257233739-3FTDG00V74GUH5GOZP48/5e-b5.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<img alt=\"5f-b6.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257235341-B3JZA9QNN7XN9H3GQVU5/5f-b6.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<img alt=\"5g-B7.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257267584-0AL4LHYWGO17E582LR61/5g-B7.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<img alt=\"5h-B8.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257267769-6E30PJJ88XG7SN3NMAVF/5h-B8.jpg\"/>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Once I was done with the balloons I added a little bow made out of the same thread I used of bows and just a touch of hot glue. I kept the sentiment super simple so that the balloons are the star of the show! Once I was done with the front I simple added a piece of scrap paper to the back to cover up my hot mess and a hand written note to wrap it up! </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1598257296900-BNBHVG1N1KGHB91XILF0/5i-Baby%2BShower%2Bcard%2Bby%2BShanna.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>What I love most about these templates is that I can make dozens of these cards with these templates and now that I have my basic design down it will be amazingly simple!!</p><p><em>Love the colors and stitching! Thanks for sharing, </em><a href=\"http://shannanoel.blogspot.com/\"><em>Shanna</em></a><em>! Shop for Amy Tangerine products at your local scrapbook stores and online at </em><a href=\"http://www.shareasale.com/r.cfm?u=530666&amp;b=199868&amp;m=24698&amp;afftrack=simon%20home%20page&amp;urllink=www%2Esimonsaysstamp%2Ecom\"><em>Simon Says Stamp</em></a><em> and </em><a href=\"http://www.shareasale.com/r.cfm?u=530666&amp;b=213361&amp;m=25838&amp;afftrack=Amy%20tangerine&amp;urllink=www%2Ebluemoonscrapbooking%2Ecom%2FCategoryProductList%2Ejsp%3Fcat%3DShop%253AManufacturers%253AAmerican%2BCrafts%3AAmerican%2BCrafts%2BAmy%2BTangerine\"><em>Blue Moon Scrapbooking</em></a><em> and </em><a href=\"http://www.shareasale.com/r.cfm?u=530666&amp;b=33086&amp;m=7429&amp;afftrack=&amp;urllink=store%2Escrapbook%2Ecom%2Fproducts%2F%3Fw%3Damy%2Btangerine\"><em>Scrapbook.com</em></a><em>. </em></p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
